Material Information Summary (Acquisition Announcement):

  • Transaction Details:
  • Binding agreement to acquire Ardgour Station land (2,880 hectares) for NZ$25M (staged).
  • NZ$5M payable in SMI shares (10-day VWAP pricing) + NZ$18M cash.

  • Non-refundable deposit: NZ$2M.

  • Key Implications:

  • Eliminates 1% gross production royalty over critical RAS orebody and adjacent deposits.
  • Secures land for Bendigo-Ophir Gold Project infrastructure (process plant, development).

  • Settlement contingent on OIO approval and Fast Track Approvals Act consents (deadline: 19 Dec 2025; 2%pa interest if extended).

  • Funding:

  • A$50M cash (as of 30 June 2025).

  • Shareholder Impact:

  • Partial share consideration requires shareholder approval.

Material Information Summary (Exploration Update - New Prospect Discovery):

  • New undrilled gold prospect (Turner) identified:
  • Gold nuggets (50+ samples, ~0.2–0.4g each) discovered at surface over 600m x 200m area within E80/4975.

  • Geological interpretation suggests aplite unit and sheared mafic contact as potential source.

  • Heritage clearance completed; earthworks commenced.

  • Diamond drilling at Martin Prospect to follow (rig en route).

  • Assay timelines:

  • First Martin Prospect RC drill assays expected mid-July 2025.

No capital raising, financials, or material tenement changes disclosed. Focus is exploration upside.

Exploration Results Announcement (Kokoseb Gold Project): - Key Highlights: - Best intercept to date: 50m at 12.00 g/t Au (including 1m at 528 g/t Au) in drill hole KRC437. - Multiple high-grade intercepts:
- 24m at 2.42 g/t Au
- 118.3m at 1.46 g/t Au (unconstrained intercept)
- 9.7m at 4.66 g/t Au (extending high-grade shoot).
- All mineralized zones remain open at depth/strike, indicating further resource growth potential.

  • Resource Impact:
  • Results will be included in upcoming Mineral Resource Estimate (MRE) scheduled for July 2025.

  • Project currently hosts 2.12Moz inferred gold resources (1.0 g/t Au cutoff).

  • Operational Context:

  • Kokoseb is located in Namibia (stable mining jurisdiction).
  • Discovery cost: <US$3/oz (industry-low).

Actionable Takeaways:
- High-grade results likely to positively impact resource upgrade and project economics.
- Potential catalyst: MRE update in July 2025 (watch for increased resource size/grade).
- Confirms continuity of mineralization, reducing geological risk.
